&lt;p&gt;South Tees Hospitals Research Department are looking for an enthusiastic motivated individual to join our Cancer Research Team as a Clinical Trials Assistant, supporting a number of dynamic research studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the research team, providing clinical and data support to ensure the successful delivery of many research trials and to provide a smooth and effective patient journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will be motivated, have excellent organisational and communication skills and be computer literate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work in a team environment that encourages collaborative team working but also supports lone working. Background knowledge in research trials is required but on the job training will be given to the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers an excellent opportunity to join a team that is committed to delivery high quality care and supports professional and personal development, also South Tees Hospitals are one of the most research-active NHS trusts in England and support a wide variety of clinical research trials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this psot will close at sufficient applicants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
